Issue: **Context leak on retry in captureWithRetry**
File: /Users/kenliu/Code/browser-comp/lib/capture-engine.mjs, lines 100-131 and 162-188

When the retry callback throws after `browser.newContext()` but before `context.close()`, the context is never closed. On each retry, a new context is opened without closing the previous one.

```js
const result = await captureWithRetry(async () => {
  const context = await browser.newContext({ ... });
  const page = await context.newPage();
  // If any of these throw, context is never closed:
  await navigateAndSettle(page, url, delay);
  await page.screenshot({ path: filepath, fullPage });
  await context.close();  // only reached on success
  return { ... };
}, label);
```

captureWithRetry retries up to MAX_RETRIES=3 times, so up to 2 leaked contexts per device per browser.

Read the actual file at /Users/kenliu/Code/browser-comp/lib/capture-engine.mjs to verify.

Return just a number 0-100 and one sentence explaining why.

